{{nihongo|'''Curriculum guidelines'''|学習指導要領|Gakushū shidō yōryō}} is a standard issued by the [[Ministry of Education, Culture, Sports, Science and Technology]]　(MEXT) that specifies materials taught at all of [[primary school|elementary]], [[middle school|junior]] and [[secondary school|senior high school]]s in [[Japan]], either [[state school|public]] or [[private school|private]]. The authority of the ministry to issue the standard is due to {{nihongo|the enforcement regulations of the [[School Education Law]]|学校教育法施行規則|Gakkō kyōiku hō shikō kisoku}}.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://law.e-gov.go.jp/htmldata/S22/S22F03501000011.html |script-title=ja:学校教育法施行規則 |language=Japanese |accessdate=2008-02-16 |date=2007-12-25 |publisher=Japanese government}}</ref> The ministry also publishes the {{nihongo|'''commentary to the curriculum guidelines'''|学習指導要領解説|Gakushū shidō yōryō kaisetsu}} that accompanies the guidelines. Nominally, the commentary is not legally binding.

== Legality ==
The legal extent of the standard has been unclear. While the standard is not a [[law]] per se, court cases in the past have shown that it is legally binding to some extent. For example, in 1990, the [[High courts of Japan|High Court]] in Fukuoka ruled that a prefectural high school lawfully fired its teacher who taught a course in a way that violated curriculum guidelines.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.courts.go.jp/search/jhsp0030?action_id=dspDetail&hanreiSrchKbn=01&hanreiNo=25867&hanreiKbn=01 |script-title=ja:判例検索システム＞検索結果詳細画面 |language=Japanese |accessdate=2008-02-16}}</ref>

