'''Eric Patrick''' is an independent filmmaker, freelance animator, Guggenheim fellow, musician, and educator. He is currently a [[tenure]]d [[professor]] in the Radio-TV-Film program at [[Northwestern University]].<ref>[http://commweb.soc.northwestern.edu/2006faculty/ School of Communication at Northwestern University :: School of Communication :: New Faculty 2006<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>
Originally from [[Port Arthur, Texas|Port Arthur]], [[Texas]], he played in a band throughout the southern United States before he studied art and film at the [[University of New Mexico]] in [[Albuquerque]].<ref>[http://www.independentexposure.com/filmmaker/274/Eric_Patrick.html Independent Exposure - Eric Patrick<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> He completed his MFA in experimental animation at [[California Institute of the Arts]] (1997).{{Citation needed|date=February 2008}}
==Films== Patrick’s films focus on low-tech, traditional, film-based techniques to explore ideas of consciousness and decay. According to the Southern Arts Federation, his films are "filled with eerily beautiful visuals that evoke a surreal, otherworldly feel which is complemented by the absence of a traditional narrative."<ref>[http://www.southarts.org/site/c.guIYLaMRJxE/b.2821367/k.840D/September_2 Southern Arts Federation - Supporting Arts in the South Since 1975 | Southern Arts Federation<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> He has been awarded grants from the [[John Simon Guggenheim Memorial Foundation]],<ref>[http://www.gf.org/06fellow.html Guggenheim Foundation 2006 Fellows Page<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081027000000/http://www.gf.org/06fellow.html |date=October 27, 2008 }}</ref> the [[Texas Filmmakers’ Production Fund]],<ref>[http://www.austinchronicle.com/gyrobase/Archive/search?searchType=archives&Search=Luke%20Savisky&Start=21 The Austin Chronicle: Search Results<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> and The [[Rooftop Film Fund]].
His films have won awards at The [[Black Maria Film Festival]],<ref>[http://www.blackmariafilmfestival.org/films.php?qs1=2007&qs2=jcho Black Maria Film Festival<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> The [[Humboldt International Film Festival]], [[Semana de Cine Experimental de Madrid]], [[South by Southwest]] Film Festival (SXSW), The [[Ann Arbor Film Festival]], [[U.S.A. Film Festival]], [[Big Muddy Film Festival]], and [[Festival de Cinema Independent de Barcelona]].<ref>[http://www.southarts.org/site/c.guIYLaMRJxE/b.2821367/k.840D/September_2007__Eric_Patrick.htm September 2007 - Eric Patrick | Southern Arts Federation<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>
His filmwork includes ''Stark Film'' (1997), ''Ablution'' (2001), and ''Startle Pattern'' (2005).
==Animation== Patrick has also worked as a commercial animator, most prominently for the [[Nickelodeon (TV channel)|Nickelodeon]] program ''[[Blue's Clues]]''. He has taught film and animation production at the [[University of Texas]] Austin, [[University of North Carolina Greensboro]], and [[Northwestern University]].<ref>[http://1uffakind.com/gallery/ericpatrick/ericpatrick.htm 1uffakind ))) gallery ))) eric patrick<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> His writing on animated documentaries and on ritual in animation have appeared in [[Animac]] journal.<ref>[http://animac.info/ANIMAC_2004/ENG/animac_magazine_04.html Animac - Magazine<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>
