[[File:The Ghana Planetarium.jpg|250px|thumb|right|The Ghana Planetarium]]
The '''Ghana Planetarium''' is located behind the Ghana Police Headquarters in [[Cantonments, Accra]]. It is open throughout the year.

The Planetarium of Accra was officially opened on Thursday January 22, 2009<ref>Ghana Science Project. [http://www.ghanascienceproject.net/ "Ghana Science Project"]</ref> by the British High Commissioner, Nicholas Westcott. Also attending were The British Council Director, The French Ambassador and the Chief of [[Nungua]] and his entourage.

