{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2016}} {{Infobox company | name = Museums of Amsterdam | logo = Logo OaM RU.png | logo_size = 250 | logo_alt = | logo_caption = | logo_padding = | image = | image_size = | image_alt = | image_caption = | trading_name = | native_name = Stichting Samenwerkende Amsterdamse Musea (SAM/OAM) | romanized_name = | former_name = | type = | traded_as = | ISIN = | industry = arts and culture; heritage | genre = | fate = | predecessor = | successor = | founded = 1994 in Amsterdam, Netherlands | founder = [[Bjorn Stenvers]] | defunct = | hq_location = [[Nieuwezijds Voorburgwal]] 359; [[Amsterdam Museum]] | hq_location_city = [[Amsterdam]] | hq_location_country = [[Netherlands]] | coordinates = | num_locations = | num_locations_year = <!-- Year of num_locations data (when known) --> | area_served = [[Amsterdam]], [[Amstelveen]], [[Zaandam]] | key_people = | products = | brands = | production = | production_year = | services = | revenue = | revenue_year = | operating_income = | income_year = | net_income = | net_income_year = | aum = | assets = | assets_year = | equity = | equity_year = | owner = | members = | members_year = | num_employees = 1 | num_employees_year = 2012 | parent = | divisions = | subsid = | slogan = | module = | ratio = | rating = | footnotes = | intl = | website = {{URL|amsterdammusea.org/en}} }}
'''Official Museums of Amsterdam''' ('''OAM''') is a consulting association of museums in [[Amsterdam]]. The organisation has existed since the eighties but it was formally founded in 1994. The organization contains both private and public museums, all of which are registered as members of [[De Museumvereniging]], the [[Dutch Museum Association]].
The OAM association has a limited jurisdiction and an elected chair and vice-chair.
The 'official' museums of Amsterdam actually do not exist. The name is a misleading translation of the unofficial name of an unincorporated meeting club of mostly government subsidized museums who co-ordinate their marketing to monopolize further government subsidies for city marketing and government assistance. The website of the Jewish Historical Museum slightly more correctly calls them: 'organization' of Amsterdam Museums with an office in the Amsterdam Uitburo or the city's entertainment desk.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.jhm.nl/organisation/joint-projects/organisation-of-amsterdam-museums/ | title= Organization of Amsterdam Museums | publisher=Jewish Historical Museum}}</ref> But the real Dutch name, as in the logo, is 'overleg' or 'meeting.'
The foundation [[Samenwerkende Amsterdamse Musea]] (SAM) represents the collective business interests of the OAM. [[Bjorn Stenvers]] was founding director of SAM from 2012 to 2017. In 2015 he founded the Amsterdam Museum Academy for museum staff trainings.<ref>Tessa Olsthoorn (5 October 2016) [http://verkeersbureaus.info/nieuws/2016/10/05/83589-eerste-amsterdam-museum-academie-certificaten-zijn-uitgereikt-in-doubletree-by-hilton-amsterdam-centraal-station/ Eerste Amsterdam Museum Academie certificaten zijn uitgereikt in DoubleTree by Hilton Amsterdam Centraal Station]. Verkeersbureaus.info. Retrieved on 24 December 2016.</ref><ref>[http://www.parool.nl/kunst-en-media/amsterdam-museum-academie-traint-museummedewerkers~a4276217/ Director Björn Stenvers launches Amsterdam Museum Academy, Parool]. Parool.nl (5 April 2016). Retrieved on 24 December 2016.</ref><ref>Janene Pieters (5 April 2016) [https://web.archive.org/web/20160405203809/http://www.nltimes.nl/2016/04/05/academy-for-museum-workers-launching-in-amsterdam/ Amsterdam museum workers to better handle disabilities, tourists]. nltimes.nl</ref><ref>[http://www.ad.nl/amsterdam/museummedewerkers-krijgen-les-over-gastvrijheid~ae48ddb5/ Museumstaff gets training in hospitality, AD]. Ad.nl (5 April 2016). Retrieved on 17 June 2017.</ref><ref>[http://www.meetingmagazine.nl/lees-meer/nieuws/9037/doubletree-by-hilton-amsterdam-centraal-station-verlengt-partnership-met-de-amsterdam-museum-academie DoubleTree by Hilton Amsterdam Centraal Station verlengt partnership met de Amsterdam Museum Academie, Meeting Magazine]. meetingmagazine.nl (9 Juni 2017). Retrieved on 19 June 2017.</ref>
The [[Marketing Overleg der Amsterdamse Musea]] (MOAM) represents the collective marketing interests of the OAM. All of the heads of marketing and communication of the forty-four partner museums are involved in MOAM. They each act as consultants, contractors, and advisers for the partner museums. The [[Museum Night (Flanders and the Netherlands)|Museum Night]] (Dutch: Museumnacht, N8) was initiated by the MOAM, but has now become an independent organisation.
